#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs0.2"
msgid "Mahāvibhaṅga"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs0.3"
msgid "Pācittiyakaṇḍa"
msgstr "The chapter on confession (<i lang=\"pli\">pācittiya</i>)"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs0.4"
msgid "Bhojanavagga"
msgstr "Monks’ Confession 32"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs0.5"
msgid "32. Gaṇabhojanasikkhāpada"
msgstr "The training rule on group meals"

#. </h1></div><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Origin story"

#. </h2><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs1.0b"
msgid ""
msgstr "First sub-story"

#. </h3><p><a class="sc" id="1"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.32.1"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.306"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa678"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs1.1"
msgid ""
"Tena samayena buddho bhagavā rājagahe viharati veḷuvane kalandakanivāpe."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying at Rājagaha in the Bamboo Grove, the "
"squirrel sanctuary."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs1.2"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena devadatto parihīnalābhasakkāro sapariso kulesu "
"viññāpetvā viññāpetvā bhuñjati."
msgstr ""
"At that time, because of decline in support and loss of respect, Devadatta "
"and his followers were only invited to meals after repeatedly asking."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs1.3"
msgid "Manussā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "People grumbled and complained,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs1.4"
msgid ""
"“kathañhi nāma samaṇā sakyaputtiyā kulesu viññāpetvā viññāpetvā bhuñjissanti."
msgstr ""
"“How can the Sakyan ascetics eat at invitations after repeatedly asking?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs1.5"
msgid "Kassa sampannaṃ na manāpaṃ, kassa sāduṃ na ruccatī”ti."
msgstr "Who doesn’t like nice food? Who doesn’t want tasty food?”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="2"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa679"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs1.6"
msgid ""
"Assosuṃ kho bhikkhū tesaṃ manussānaṃ ujjhāyantānaṃ khiyyantānaṃ vipācentānaṃ."
msgstr "The monks heard those people grumbling and complaining,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs1.7"
msgid "Ye te bhikkhū appicchā … pe …"
msgstr "and the monks of few desires …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs1.8"
msgid "te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "complained and criticized those monks,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs1.9"
msgid ""
"“kathañhi nāma devadatto sapariso kulesu viññāpetvā viññāpetvā bhuñjissatī”"
"ti … pe …"
msgstr ""
"“How can Devadatta and his followers eat at invitations after repeatedly "
"asking?” …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs1.10"
msgid ""
"“saccaṃ kira tvaṃ, devadatta, sapariso kulesu viññāpetvā viññāpetvā "
"bhuñjasī”ti?"
msgstr "“Is it true, Devadatta, that you do this?”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs1.11"
msgid "“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti."
msgstr "“It’s true, Master.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs1.12"
msgid "Vigarahi buddho bhagavā … pe …"
msgstr "The Buddha rebuked him, “…"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs1.13"
msgid ""
"kathañhi nāma tvaṃ, moghapurisa, sapariso kulesu viññāpetvā viññāpetvā "
"bhuñjissasi."
msgstr ""
"Foolish man, how can you and your followers eat at invitations after "
"repeatedly asking?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs1.14"
msgid "Netaṃ, moghapurisa, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya … pe …"
msgstr "This will not give rise to confidence in those without it …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs1.15"
msgid "evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. </p><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs1.15a"
msgid ""
msgstr "First preliminary ruling"

#. </h3><p><a class="sc" id="3"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.307"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa680"></a>
#. <span class="rule"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs1.16"
msgid "“Gaṇabhojane pācittiyan”ti."
msgstr ""
"‘If a monk eats in a group, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”"

#. </span>
#. </p><p class="endsection"><a class="sc" id="4"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa681"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs1.17"
msgid "Evañcidaṃ bhagavatā bhikkhūnaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ paññattaṃ hoti."
msgstr "In this way the Master laid down this training rule for the monks."

#. </p><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs2.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Second sub-story"

#. </h3><p><a class="sc" id="5"></a><a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli4.72"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.32.2"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa682"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs2.1"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena manussā gilāne bhikkhū bhattena nimantenti."
msgstr "Soon afterwards people invited sick monks to a meal."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs2.2"
msgid ""
"Bhikkhū kukkuccāyantā nādhivāsenti—“paṭikkhittaṃ bhagavatā gaṇabhojanan”ti."
msgstr ""
"Knowing that the Master had prohibited eating meals in a group and being "
"afraid of wrongdoing, they did not accept."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs2.3"
msgid "Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ."
msgstr "They told the Master."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs2.4"
msgid ""
"Atha kho bhagavā etasmiṃ nidāne etasmiṃ pakaraṇe dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā "
"bhikkhū āmantesi—"
msgstr "Soon afterwards he gave a teaching and addressed the monks,"

#. <span class="rule"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs2.5"
msgid "“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, gilānena bhikkhunā gaṇabhojanaṃ bhuñjituṃ."
msgstr "“Monks, I allow a sick monk to eat in a group."

#. </span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs2.6"
msgid "Evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And so, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. </p><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs2.6a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Second preliminary ruling"

#. </h3><p><a class="sc" id="6"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa683"></a>
#. <span class="rule"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs2.7"
msgid "“Gaṇabhojane, aññatra samayā, pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"‘If a monk eats in a group, unless there is an appropriate reason, he "
"commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs2.8"
msgid "Tatthāyaṃ samayo."
msgstr "The appropriate reason is this:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs2.9"
msgid "Gilānasamayo—ayaṃ tattha samayo”ti."
msgstr "he is sick.’”"

#. </span></p><p class="endsection"><a class="sc" id="7"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa684"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs2.10"
msgid "Evañcidaṃ bhagavatā bhikkhūnaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ paññattaṃ hoti."
msgstr "In this way the Master laid down this training rule for the monks."

#. </p><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs3.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Third sub-story"

#. </h3><p><a class="sc" id="8"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.32.3"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa685"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs3.1"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena manussā cīvaradānasamaye sacīvarabhattaṃ paṭiyādetvā "
"bhikkhū nimantenti—"
msgstr ""
"Soon afterwards, during the robe-giving season, people prepared a meal "
"together with robe-cloth and then invited the monks, saying,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs3.2"
msgid "“bhojetvā cīvarena acchādessāmā”ti."
msgstr "“We wish to offer you a meal and then give you robe-cloth.”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs3.3"
msgid ""
"Bhikkhū kukkuccāyantā nādhivāsenti—“paṭikkhittaṃ bhagavatā gaṇabhojanan”ti."
msgstr ""
"Knowing that the Master had prohibited eating meals in a group and being "
"afraid of wrongdoing, they did not accept."

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.308"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs3.4"
msgid "Cīvaraṃ parittaṃ uppajjati."
msgstr "As a result they only obtained a small amount of robe-cloth."

#. VAR: Bhagavato → bhikkhū bhagavato (c1)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs3.5"
msgid "Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ … pe …"
msgstr "They told the Master. …"

#. <span class="rule"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs3.6"
msgid "anujānāmi, bhikkhave, cīvaradānasamaye gaṇabhojanaṃ bhuñjituṃ."
msgstr "“Monks, I allow you to eat in a group during the robe-giving season."

#. </span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs3.7"
msgid "Evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And so, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. </p><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs3.7a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Third preliminary ruling"

#. </h3><p><a class="sc" id="9"></a>
#. <span class="rule"><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa686"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs3.8"
msgid "“Gaṇabhojane, aññatra samayā, pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"‘If a monk eats in a group, unless there is an appropriate reason, he "
"commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs3.9"
msgid "Tatthāyaṃ samayo."
msgstr "The appropriate reasons are these:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs3.10"
msgid "Gilānasamayo, cīvaradānasamayo—ayaṃ tattha samayo”ti."
msgstr "he is sick, it is the robe-giving season.’”"

#. </span></p><p class="endsection"><a class="sc" id="10"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa687"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs3.11"
msgid "Evañcidaṃ bhagavatā bhikkhūnaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ paññattaṃ hoti."
msgstr "In this way the Master laid down this training rule for the monks."

#. </p><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs4.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Fourth sub-story"

#. </h3><p><a class="sc" id="11"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.32.4"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa688"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs4.1"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena manussā cīvarakārake bhikkhū bhattena nimantenti."
msgstr "Soon afterwards people invited monks who were making a robe for a meal."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs4.2"
msgid ""
"Bhikkhū kukkuccāyantā nādhivāsenti—“paṭikkhittaṃ bhagavatā gaṇabhojanan”ti."
msgstr ""
"Knowing that the Master had prohibited eating meals in a group and being "
"afraid of wrongdoing, they did not accept."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs4.3"
msgid "Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ … pe …"
msgstr "They told the Master. …"

#. <span class="rule"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs4.4"
msgid "anujānāmi, bhikkhave, cīvarakārasamaye gaṇabhojanaṃ bhuñjituṃ."
msgstr "“Monks, I allow you to eat in a group when you are making a robe."

#. </span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs4.5"
msgid "Evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And so, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. </p><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs4.5a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Fourth preliminary ruling"

#. </h3><p><a class="sc" id="12"></a>
#. <span class="rule"><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa689"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs4.6"
msgid "“Gaṇabhojane, aññatra samayā, pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"‘If a monk eats in a group, unless there is an appropriate reason, he "
"commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs4.7"
msgid "Tatthāyaṃ samayo."
msgstr "The appropriate reasons are these:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs4.8"
msgid "Gilānasamayo, cīvaradānasamayo, cīvarakārasamayo—ayaṃ tattha samayo”ti."
msgstr "he is sick, it is the robe-giving season, he is making a robe.’”"

#. </span></p><p class="endsection"><a class="sc" id="13"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa690"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs4.9"
msgid "Evañcidaṃ bhagavatā bhikkhūnaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ paññattaṃ hoti."
msgstr "In this way the Master laid down this training rule for the monks."

#. </p><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs5.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Fifth sub-story"

#. </h3><p><a class="sc" id="14"></a><a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli4.73"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.32.5"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa691"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs5.1"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhū manussehi saddhiṃ addhānaṃ gacchanti."
msgstr "Soon afterwards monks went traveling on a main road with some people."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs5.2"
msgid "Atha kho te bhikkhū te manusse etadavocuṃ—"
msgstr "The monks said to the people,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs5.3"
msgid "“muhuttaṃ, āvuso, āgametha; piṇḍāya carissāmā”ti."
msgstr "“Please wait a moment while we walk for alms.”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs5.4"
msgid "Te evamāhaṃsu—"
msgstr "They replied,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs5.5"
msgid "“idheva, bhante, bhuñjathā”ti."
msgstr "“Venerables, please eat right here.”"

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.309"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs5.6"
msgid ""
"Bhikkhū kukkuccāyantā na paṭiggaṇhanti—“paṭikkhittaṃ bhagavatā "
"gaṇabhojanan”ti."
msgstr ""
"Knowing that the Master had prohibited eating meals in a group and being "
"afraid of wrongdoing, they did not accept."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs5.7"
msgid "Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ … pe …"
msgstr "They told the Master. …"

#. <span class="rule"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs5.8"
msgid "anujānāmi, bhikkhave, addhānagamanasamaye gaṇabhojanaṃ bhuñjituṃ."
msgstr ""
"“Monks, I allow you to eat in a group when you are traveling on a main road."

#. </span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs5.9"
msgid "Evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And so, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. </p><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs5.9a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Fifth preliminary ruling"

#. </h3><p><a class="sc" id="15"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa692"></a>
#. <span class="rule"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs5.10"
msgid "“Gaṇabhojane, aññatra samayā, pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"‘If a monk eats in a group, unless there is an appropriate reason, he "
"commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs5.11"
msgid "Tatthāyaṃ samayo."
msgstr "The appropriate reasons are these:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs5.12"
msgid ""
"Gilānasamayo, cīvaradānasamayo, cīvarakārasamayo, addhānagamanasamayo—ayaṃ "
"tattha samayo”ti."
msgstr ""
"he is sick, it is the robe-giving season, he is making a robe, he is "
"traveling on a main road.’”"

#. </span></p><p class="endsection"><a class="sc" id="16"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa693"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs5.13"
msgid "Evañcidaṃ bhagavatā bhikkhūnaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ paññattaṃ hoti."
msgstr "In this way the Master laid down this training rule for the monks."

#. </p><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs6.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Sixth sub-story"

#. </h3><p><a class="sc" id="17"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.32.6"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa694"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs6.1"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhū manussehi saddhiṃ nāvāya gacchanti."
msgstr "Soon afterwards monks boarded a boat with some people."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs6.2"
msgid "Atha kho te bhikkhū te manusse etadavocuṃ—"
msgstr "The monks said to the people,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs6.3"
msgid "“muhuttaṃ, āvuso, tīraṃ upanetha; piṇḍāya carissāmā”ti."
msgstr "“Please go to the shore for a moment while we walk for alms.”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs6.4"
msgid "Te evamāhaṃsu—"
msgstr "They replied,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs6.5"
msgid "“idheva, bhante, bhuñjathā”ti."
msgstr "“Venerables, please eat right here.”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs6.6"
msgid ""
"Bhikkhū kukkuccāyantā na paṭiggaṇhanti—“paṭikkhittaṃ bhagavatā "
"gaṇabhojanan”ti."
msgstr ""
"Knowing that the Master had prohibited eating meals in a group and being "
"afraid of wrongdoing, they did not accept."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs6.7"
msgid "Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ … pe …"
msgstr "They told the Master. …"

#. <span class="rule"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs6.8"
msgid "anujānāmi, bhikkhave, nāvābhiruhanasamaye gaṇabhojanaṃ bhuñjituṃ."
msgstr "“Monks, I allow you to eat in a group when you are traveling by boat."

#. </span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs6.9"
msgid "Evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And so, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. </p><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs6.9a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Sixth preliminary ruling"

#. </h3><p><a class="sc" id="18"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa695"></a>
#. <span class="rule"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs6.10"
msgid "“Gaṇabhojane, aññatra samayā, pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"‘If a monk eats in a group, unless there is an appropriate reason, he "
"commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs6.11"
msgid "Tatthāyaṃ samayo."
msgstr "The appropriate reasons are these:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs6.12"
msgid ""
"Gilānasamayo, cīvaradānasamayo, cīvarakārasamayo, addhānagamanasamayo, "
"nāvābhiruhanasamayo—ayaṃ tattha samayo”ti."
msgstr ""
"he is sick, it is the robe-giving season, he is making a robe, he is "
"traveling on a main road, he is traveling by boat.’”"

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="19"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa696"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs6.13"
msgid "Evañcidaṃ bhagavatā bhikkhūnaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ paññattaṃ hoti."
msgstr "In this way the Master laid down this training rule for the monks."

#. </p><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs7.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Seventh sub-story"

#. </h3><p class="endsection"><a class="sc" id="20"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.32.7"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa697"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs7.1"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena disāsu vassaṃvuṭṭhā bhikkhū rājagahaṃ āgacchanti "
"bhagavantaṃ dassanāya."
msgstr ""
"Soon afterwards monks who had completed the rainy-season residence in "
"various regions were coming to Rājagaha to see the Master."

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.310"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs7.2"
msgid "Manussā nānāverajjake bhikkhū passitvā bhattena nimantenti."
msgstr ""
"People saw those monks who had come from various countries, and they invited "
"them for a meal."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs7.3"
msgid ""
"Bhikkhū kukkuccāyantā nādhivāsenti—“paṭikkhittaṃ bhagavatā gaṇabhojanan”ti."
msgstr ""
"Knowing that the Master had prohibited eating meals in a group and being "
"afraid of wrongdoing, they did not accept."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs7.4"
msgid "Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ … pe …"
msgstr "They told the Master. …"

#. <span class="rule"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs7.5"
msgid "anujānāmi, bhikkhave, mahāsamaye gaṇabhojanaṃ bhuñjituṃ."
msgstr "“Monks, I allow you to eat in a group on big occasions."

#. </span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs7.6"
msgid "Evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And so, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. </p><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs7.6a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Seventh preliminary ruling"

#. </h3><p><a class="sc" id="21"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa698"></a>
#. <span class="rule"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs7.7"
msgid "“Gaṇabhojane, aññatra samayā, pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"‘If a monk eats in a group, unless there is an appropriate reason, he "
"commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs7.8"
msgid "Tatthāyaṃ samayo."
msgstr "The appropriate reasons are these:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs7.9"
msgid ""
"Gilānasamayo, cīvaradānasamayo, cīvarakārasamayo, addhānagamanasamayo, "
"nāvābhiruhanasamayo, mahāsamayo—ayaṃ tattha samayo”ti."
msgstr ""
"he is sick, it is the robe-giving season, he is making a robe, he is "
"traveling on a main road, he is traveling by boat, it is a big occasion.’”"

#. </span></p><p class="endsection"><a class="sc" id="22"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa699"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs7.10"
msgid "Evañcidaṃ bhagavatā bhikkhūnaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ paññattaṃ hoti."
msgstr "In this way the Master laid down this training rule for the monks."

#. </p><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs8.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Eighth sub-story"

#. </h3><p><a class="sc" id="23"></a><a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli4.74"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.32.8"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa700"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs8.1"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena rañño māgadhassa seniyassa bimbisārassa ñātisālohito "
"ājīvakesu pabbajito hoti."
msgstr ""
"Soon afterwards a relative of King Seniya Bimbisāra of Magadha who had gone "
"forth with the Ājīvaka ascetics"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs8.2"
msgid "Atha kho so ājīvako yena rājā māgadho seniyo bimbisāro tenupasaṅkami;"
msgstr "approached the King"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs8.3"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā rājānaṃ māgadhaṃ seniyaṃ bimbisāraṃ etadavoca—"
msgstr "and said,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs8.4"
msgid "“icchāmahaṃ, mahārāja, sabbapāsaṇḍikabhattaṃ kātun”ti."
msgstr "“Great King, I wish to make a meal for the ascetics of all sects.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs8.5"
msgid ""
"“Sace tvaṃ, bhante, buddhappamukhaṃ bhikkhusaṃghaṃ paṭhamaṃ bhojeyyāsi”."
msgstr ""
"“That’s fine, Venerable, if you first feed the Order of monks headed by the "
"Buddha.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs8.6"
msgid "“Evaṃ kareyyāmī”ti."
msgstr "“I’ll do that.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs8.7"
msgid "Atha kho so ājīvako bhikkhūnaṃ santike dūtaṃ pāhesi—"
msgstr "And he sent a message to the monks:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs8.8"
msgid "“adhivāsentu me bhikkhū svātanāya bhattan”ti."
msgstr "“Please accept a meal from me tomorrow.”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs8.9"
msgid ""
"Bhikkhū kukkuccāyantā nādhivāsenti—“paṭikkhittaṃ bhagavatā gaṇabhojanan”ti."
msgstr ""
"But knowing that the Master had prohibited eating meals in a group and being "
"afraid of wrongdoing, they did not accept."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs8.10"
msgid "Atha kho so ājīvako yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami;"
msgstr "That Ājīvaka ascetic then went to the Master,"

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.311"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs8.11"
msgid ""
"upasaṅkamitvā bhagavatā saddhiṃ sammodi, sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ "
"vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ aṭṭhāsi."
msgstr "exchanged friendly greetings with him, and stood to one side."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs8.12"
msgid "Ekamantaṃ ṭhito kho so ājīvako bhagavantaṃ etadavoca—"
msgstr "And he said this,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs8.13"
msgid "“bhavampi gotamo pabbajito, ahampi pabbajito;"
msgstr "“Good Gotama has gone forth and so have I."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs8.14"
msgid "arahati pabbajito pabbajitassa piṇḍaṃ paṭiggahetuṃ."
msgstr ""
"One who has gone forth is entitled to give alms to another who has gone "
"forth."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs8.15"
msgid ""
"Adhivāsetu me bhavaṃ gotamo svātanāya bhattaṃ saddhiṃ bhikkhusaṃghenā”ti."
msgstr ""
"Good Gotama, please accept a meal from me tomorrow together with the Order "
"of monks.”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs8.16"
msgid "Adhivāsesi bhagavā tuṇhībhāvena."
msgstr "The Master consented by remaining silent."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs8.17"
msgid "Atha kho so ājīvako bhagavato adhivāsanaṃ viditvā pakkāmi."
msgstr "The Ājīvaka understood that the Master had consented, and he left."

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs8.18"
msgid ""
"Atha kho bhagavā etasmiṃ nidāne etasmiṃ pakaraṇe dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā "
"bhikkhū āmantesi—"
msgstr "Soon afterwards the Master gave a teaching and addressed the monks,"

#. <span class="rule"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs8.19"
msgid "“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, samaṇabhattasamaye gaṇabhojanaṃ bhuñjituṃ."
msgstr ""
"“Monks, I allow you to eat in a group when the meal is given by an ascetic."

#. </span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs8.20"
msgid "Evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And so, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs8.20a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Final ruling"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="24"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa701"></a>
#. <span class="rule"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs8.21"
msgid "Gaṇabhojane, aññatra samayā, pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"‘If a monk eats in a group, unless there is an appropriate reason, he "
"commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs8.22"
msgid "Tatthāyaṃ samayo."
msgstr "The appropriate reasons are these:"

#. VAR: nāvābhiruhanasamayo → nāvābhirūhana ... (bj, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs8.23"
msgid ""
"Gilānasamayo, cīvaradānasamayo, cīvarakārasamayo, addhānagamanasamayo, "
"nāvābhiruhanasamayo, mahāsamayo, samaṇabhattasamayo—ayaṃ tattha samayo”ti."
msgstr ""
"he is sick, it is the robe-giving season, he is making a robe, he is "
"traveling on a main road, he is traveling by boat, it is a big occasion, it "
"is a meal given by an ascetic.’”"

#. </span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs8.24"
msgid "(<em>32</em>:<strong>81</strong>)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs9.1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Definitions"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="25"></a><a class="pts-cs-empty" id="bu-pc.32.9"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.32.9.1"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa702"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs9.1.1"
msgid "Gaṇabhojanaṃ nāma"
msgstr "Eats in a group:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs9.1.2"
msgid ""
"yattha cattāro bhikkhū pañcannaṃ bhojanānaṃ aññatarena bhojanena nimantitā "
"bhuñjanti."
msgstr ""
"wherever four monks, after being invited, eat any of the five staple foods—"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs9.1.3"
msgid "Etaṃ gaṇabhojanaṃ nāma."
msgstr "this is called “eats in a group."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="26"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa703"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs9.1.4"
msgid "Aññatra samayāti"
msgstr "Unless there is an appropriate reason:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs9.1.5"
msgid "ṭhapetvā samayaṃ."
msgstr "except at an appropriate time."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="27"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa704"></a> 
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs9.1.6"
msgid "Gilānasamayo nāma"
msgstr "He is sick:"

#. </span><span class="gloss">
#. VAR: phalitā → phālitā (bj, s1-3, pts1, mr)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs9.1.7"
msgid "antamaso pādāpi phalitā honti."
msgstr "even if he just has split feet,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs9.1.8"
msgid "“Gilānasamayo”ti bhuñjitabbaṃ."
msgstr "he may eat in a group."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="28"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa705"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs9.1.9"
msgid "Cīvaradānasamayo nāma"
msgstr "It is the robe-giving season:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"><a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.312"></a>
#. That is, the last month of the rainy season, plus the four months of the cold season. 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs9.1.10"
msgid ""
"anatthate kathine vassānassa pacchimo māso, atthate kathine pañcamāsā. "
"“Cīvaradānasamayo”ti bhuñjitabbaṃ."
msgstr ""
"if he has not done the robe-making ceremony, he may eat in a group during "
"the last month of the rainy season. If he has done the robe-making ceremony, "
"he may eat in a group during the five month period."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="29"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa706"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs9.1.11"
msgid "Cīvarakārasamayo nāma"
msgstr "He is making a robe:"

#. </span><span class="gloss">
#. According to the commentary, <ref>Sp.4.813.4</ref>, “Whoever does any work to be done in regard to the robe—the Mahāpaccariya says, ‘Even one who just threads the needle’—may eat a group meal because he is making a robe,” <i lang="pli">yo tattha cīvare kattabbaṃ yaṃkiñci kammaṃ karoti, mahāpaccariyañhi “antamaso sūcivedhanako”tipi vuttaṃ, tena cīvarakārasamayoti bhuñjitabbaṃ</i>. 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs9.1.12"
msgid "cīvare kayiramāne."
msgstr "if he is making a robe,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs9.1.13"
msgid "“Cīvarakārasamayo”ti bhuñjitabbaṃ."
msgstr "he may eat in a group."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="30"></a><a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli4.75"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa707"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs9.1.14"
msgid "Addhānagamanasamayo nāma"
msgstr "He is traveling on a main road:"

#. </span><span class="gloss">
#. Half a <i lang="pli">yojana</i>. The length of a <i lang="pli">yojana</i> is uncertain, and perhaps it never was a precise distance. But a reasonable estimate is 8 miles or just under 13 kilometers (see ACMC, p.16). Thus half a <i lang="pli">yojana</i> is just over 6 km. 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs9.1.15"
msgid ""
"“addhayojanaṃ gacchissāmī”ti bhuñjitabbaṃ, gacchantena bhuñjitabbaṃ, gatena "
"bhuñjitabbaṃ."
msgstr ""
"if he intends to travel at least six kilometers, he may eat in a group. And "
"he may eat in a group while he is traveling, and after traveling."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="31"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa708"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs9.1.16"
msgid "Nāvābhiruhanasamayo nāma"
msgstr "He is traveling by boat:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs9.1.17"
msgid ""
"“nāvaṃ abhiruhissāmī”ti bhuñjitabbaṃ, āruḷhena bhuñjitabbaṃ, oruḷhena "
"bhuñjitabbaṃ."
msgstr ""
"if he intends to board a boat, he may eat in a group. And he may eat in a "
"group while on-board, and after disembarking."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="32"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa709"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs9.1.18"
msgid "Mahāsamayo nāma"
msgstr "It is a big occasion:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs9.1.19"
msgid ""
"yattha dve tayo bhikkhū piṇḍāya caritvā yāpenti, catutthe āgate na yāpenti."
msgstr ""
"if two or three monks can get by by walking for alms, but not a group of "
"four,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs9.1.20"
msgid "“Mahāsamayo”ti bhuñjitabbaṃ."
msgstr "he may eat in a group."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="33"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa710"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs9.1.21"
msgid "Samaṇabhattasamayo nāma"
msgstr "It is a meal given by an ascetic:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs9.1.22"
msgid "yo koci paribbājakasamāpanno bhattaṃ karoti."
msgstr "if any kind of wanderer is making the meal,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs9.1.23"
msgid "“Samaṇabhattasamayo”ti bhuñjitabbaṃ."
msgstr "he may eat in a group."

#. </span>
#. </p><hr><p><a class="sc" id="34"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa711"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs9.1.24"
msgid "“Aññatra samayā bhuñjissāmī”ti paṭiggaṇhāti, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"If he receives it intending to eat it, unless there is an appropriate "
"reason, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs9.1.25"
msgid "Ajjhohāre ajjhohāre āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr "For every mouthful, he commits an offense entailing confession."

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs9.2.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Permutations"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="35"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.32.9.2"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa712"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs9.2.1"
msgid ""
"Gaṇabhojane gaṇabhojanasaññī, aññatra samayā, bhuñjati, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"If it is a group meal, and he perceives it as a group meal, and he eats, "
"unless there is an appropriate reason, he commits an offense entailing "
"confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs9.2.2"
msgid "Gaṇabhojane vematiko, aññatra samayā, bhuñjati, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"If it is a group meal, but he is unsure if it is, and he eats, unless there "
"is an appropriate reason, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs9.2.3"
msgid ""
"Gaṇabhojane nagaṇabhojanasaññī, aññatra samayā, bhuñjati, āpatti "
"pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"If it is a group meal, but he does not perceive it as a group meal, and he "
"eats, unless there is an appropriate reason, he commits an offense entailing "
"confession."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="36"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa713"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs9.2.4"
msgid "Nagaṇabhojane gaṇabhojanasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"If it is not a group meal, but he perceives it as a group meal, he commits "
"an offense of wrong conduct."

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.313"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs9.2.5"
msgid "Nagaṇabhojane vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"If it is not a group meal, but he is unsure of it, he commits an offense of "
"wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs9.2.6"
msgid "Nagaṇabhojane nagaṇabhojanasaññī, anāpatti."
msgstr ""
"If it is not a group meal, and he does not perceive it as a group meal, "
"there is no offense."

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs9.3.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Non-offenses"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="37"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.32.9.3"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa714"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs9.3.1"
msgid "Anāpatti—"
msgstr "There is no offense:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs9.3.2"
msgid "samaye,"
msgstr "if there is an appropriate reason;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs9.3.3"
msgid "dve tayo ekato bhuñjanti,"
msgstr "if two or three eat together;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs9.3.4"
msgid "piṇḍāya caritvā ekato sannipatitvā bhuñjanti,"
msgstr "if they eat together after walking for alms;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs9.3.5"
msgid "salākabhattaṃ,"
msgstr "if it is a regular meal invitation;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs9.3.6"
msgid "niccabhattaṃ,"
msgstr "if it is a meal invitation decided by drawing lots;"

#. One of the sub-commentaries says: <i lang="pli">Ekasmiṃ pakkhe ekadivasaṃ dātabbaṃ bhattaṃ pakkhikaṃ</i>, “<i lang="pli">pakkhikaṃ</i> means: meal to be given one day in one half-month.” (Sp-ṭ.2.30).
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs9.3.7"
msgid "pakkhikaṃ,"
msgstr "if it is a half-monthly meal;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs9.3.8"
msgid "uposathikaṃ,"
msgstr "if it is on the observance day;"

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.314"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs9.3.9"
msgid "pāṭipadikaṃ,"
msgstr "if it is on the day after the observance day;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs9.3.10"
msgid "pañca bhojanāni ṭhapetvā sabbattha anāpatti,"
msgstr "if it is anything apart from the five staple foods;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs9.3.11"
msgid "ummattakassa,"
msgstr "if he is insane;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs9.3.12"
msgid "ādikammikassāti."
msgstr "if he is the first offender."

#. </p><hr><p class="endsutta"><a class="sc" id="38"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa715"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:pts-cs9.3.13"
msgid "Gaṇabhojanasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ dutiyaṃ."
msgstr "The second rule, the training rule on group meals, is finished."

